# BidPazar Full-Stack Component Structure

## Project Organization
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── (auth)/            # Authentication routes
│   ├── (dashboard)/       # Dashboard routes
│   ├── api/               # API routes
│   └── layout.tsx         # Root layout
├── components/            # Reusable components
│   ├── ui/               # UI components
│   ├── forms/            # Form components
│   └── shared/           # Shared components
├── lib/                  # Utility functions and services
│   ├── auth/            # Authentication utilities
│   ├── db/              # Database utilities
│   ├── websocket/       # WebSocket utilities
│   └── webrtc/          # WebRTC utilities
└── types/               # TypeScript types
```

## Core Components
- **Layout**: Base page structure, navigation, footer
- **Auth**: Sign-in/sign-up forms, password reset, verification
- **Product**: Listing cards, details, image galleries
- **LiveStream**: Stream viewer, controls, chat interface
- **Auction**: Bid controls, countdown timer, pricing display
- **User**: Profile, dashboard, account settings
- **Messaging**: Chat interface, conversation list, message bubbles
- **Admin**: Dashboard, user management, content moderation

## API Routes Structure
```
src/app/api/
├── auth/                # Authentication endpoints
├── products/           # Product endpoints
├── users/             # User endpoints
├── messages/          # Message endpoints
├── streams/           # Stream endpoints
└── rtc/               # WebRTC endpoints
```

## Component Patterns
- Server vs. Client components
- Route Handlers for API endpoints
- Controlled forms with React Hook Form
- Error boundaries for fault tolerance
- Loading states and skeletons
- Modals and overlays
- Responsive layouts with Tailwind breakpoints

## State Management
- React Context for global state
- Custom hooks for shared logic
- Form state with React Hook Form
- API data fetching with SWR pattern
- WebSocket event handling
- Server-side state with Next.js

## Styling Approach
- TailwindCSS utility classes
- Component variants with class-variance-authority
- Global styles in globals.css
- Design tokens for consistency
- Responsive breakpoints

